caption: Lovely experience.  The restraunt provided chill and classy vibes with excellent service from our waiter Georgi.  Food was spectacular with plenty of vegan and non vegan options.

Take advantage of the Happy Gyro pop-up to get street food from a Michelin star restaurant. Grab friends and buy everything. The standout sides: fig and beet salad, baked ziti, olive oil gelato with chocolate cookie crumbs. The wraps/sandwiches were also great, my favorites were the Reuben and lamb.

Not only is that 32 dollar  pizza is worth every cent, Happy Gyro is the only incarnation of any of DC's michelin star restaurants that  provides the same excellence in carry out form. Hospitality and flavor. Truly the best we have in town right now, absolutely anyone who can indulge in these pies and pints must.

This review is for Happy Gryo - unique vegetarian dishes bursting with flavor, the Gryo and crispy zucchini fritters are my favorites!  Zucchini fritters (5/5) Hands-down the best, make room for the appetizer! The crispy fritters had a nice crispy shell stuffed with shredded zucchini and creamy yogurt and feta cheese.  Gryo  (4/5) - Fun and interesting meaty texture made of very thinly sliced shredded crispy tofu with pickled peppers and creamy tzatziki in a pillowy housemade pita. All the flavors blended well together with this innovative dish. The pita wasn't overstuffed and surprisingly not messy, my hubby and I had no problem eating the wraps in the car.  Fryo (3/5) - Crispy french fries stuffed in a pita with tzatziki sauce. It was fun to try, but nothing special. Prefer the Gyro over the Fryo.  Seasonal popsicles (3/5) - Hit/miss depending on the flavor and not quite what I expected. The Vanilla Pecan Dark Chocolate had a tasty dark chocolate pecan shell and had a strong coconut flavor. I preferred the Vanilla Pecan Dark Chocolate over the Fig Greek Yogurt with a bold fig flavor and some notes of ginger. The flavors didn't quite fuse that well with a bit of inconsistency. It was fun to try the homemade popiscles. Pleasant Pops on U street are my favorite!  The innovative dishes loaded with veggies are fun to try and packed with some great flavor. My hubby and I enjoyed the vegetarian feast in our car. If you're looking for something different, give Happy Gryo a go. Lives up to its name!
Best takeout meal since Covid. Pizza was excellent

The Food was good but not the best ive ever had but at the end of a 500 dollar bill with wine tasting they offered us coffee but then charged us for it. What a way to end an amazing meal on an sour note.
Komi is the best!
A great experience.
Fantastic meal, phenomenal service.
Only thing to say is once they allow you to dine at this delicious restaurant you will never forget it
Komi has the best dinner in DC. They always go out of their way to take care of you, and the food is second to none.

Just had my first Komi experience and it was hands down the best meal I’ve had in my life. My boyfriend and I are making our way through the DC Michelin Star places and decided to try Komi for a belated Valentines dinner. Komi has been the best thus far with zero competition from the others. There’s just no comparison, and the fact that it was almost half the cost of Pineapple & Pearls made it that much better. I have to comment on how amazing the staff is first. Kyle was attentive, hilarious, and knowledgeable. I didn’t catch the name of the woman helping us but she had short brown hair and was just wonderful.  The first 4-5 courses are small but so delightfully balanced and flavorful with simple and fresh ingredients. The figs were to die for and so were the scallops. The pasta we were told is handmade every day and was the best I’ve ever had. Everything was perfectly seasoned and it was timed incredibly well. My partner and I don’t drink but they brought us a non alcoholic drink to try that was just incredible. Everything they brought was better than the last. The desserts at the end were just a perfect finish to the most incredible meal. Can’t wait to go back.

The service The service The service The staff. The staff. The food is fine, no doubt. You'd expect that at this price level. But the service and the staff. They make this place.  Go there. Enjoy a fine dining experience, amazing food, and one of the best service experiences DC has to offer.
Really impressed. Come hungry, there is a lot of food even for a tasting menu.

Amazing dinner experience that offered a lot of familiar flavors, but with an elevated twist. My husband and I split the wine pairing and got to enjoy a nice variety. Although the dishes came out slow, we had a great time and came home with leftovers.
So beyond excellent I don’t even know where to start. The service and food was phenomenal!

Love, love, love Komi! The food is ALWAYS on point and amazing flavors in small bites. This visit was our second gyro visit...all vegan and started with tacos and ended with gyros and fillet of fish...all vegan.  Nights at Komi and Gyro are always special. Do the wine pairings. Anne and Johnny are fabulous!!
Went for the Happy Gyro popup. It did not disappoint. Monis and his staff deliver a superlative experience.
We went during their pop-up called Happy Gyro. Amazing food, creative and clever.
Fantastic!  The food was delicious and the service superb!
Went during Happy Gyro and loved the vegetarian menu!
The food was delicious and unique. We went during Happy Gyro and loved all the vegetarian food!
Beautiful set up great tasting food
Komi is incredible. A one-of-a-kind experience. The food, the atmosphere, the service - you have to try this.

This place is not really convincing for European tastes. Food combination without interest, too salty, too sweet; informal is fun but.... paper towels?, basic cutlery and fair, efficient service - not once have we been asked if we liked the food, far too noisy. Not quite going back

Amazing dining experience. Went here with family for my wife's birthday, for their 'Happy Gyro' special. Everything was vegetarian and everything was excellent! Great creative drink pairings too. Amazing service. Definitely a 'must visit' restaurant for a special occasion.
Finest food experience in DC

My husband and I went to this place during a business trip to DC. Didn't know it is a Michelin Star restaurant. It was one of the best dining experiences we have ever had.  Food was exceptional, wine was excellent, the staff was amazing, and the  restaurant itself was understated and comfortable. Can only highly recommend this place to everyone.

Unbelievable experience.  Wife and I took a quick trip to DC, with a last minute trip we didn't really think about reservations for places until it was too late. We managed to sneak a 9pm booking on a friday here and it was hands down the best experience of the weekend (and top 5 in my life). 12-13 courses I think, no beverage pairing but it wasn't needed.  The beer manager knows his $&#* when it comes to Sours and other beers.  Had some great recommendations and my wife enjoyed the wine menu.  I am not even sure how to describe the food.  elegant and simple, but complex and so so delicious.  One of the funnier ones to stand out was a simple salad but it was very good.  The main entree was cabrito (goat) and usually when you have a tasting menu you can leave a little hungry.  Not here - The entree dish alone could have been enough.  We were struggling to get it all down.  On top of that, having talked with the server about being from Texas they sent out some pulled pork from the kitchen as well.  Can't say enough good things about this place and their staff.  For sure will be getting reservations in advance next time, and will hit it up any time we are in the area.  Do not miss this experience, if you love food and an amazing atmosphere and service.
Fantastic dining experience. Obviously quite expensive, but the food and service were worth it.

fun big place with the family! will be back.

Went to Komi for the first time as a special occasion.  I made reservations about a month in advance and was slightly limited on the traditional dinner times.  I was still able to get an 8:30PM reservation which wasn't too bad, especially on a weekend.  The dress code was a step up from business casual.  Dressy casual would be accurate.  I wore slacks, dress shoes, and a button up tucked in and did not feel underdressed.  No jacket or tie.  The courses and presentation altogether will take time.  We left around 11:30PM and were completely satisfied.  This is my second Michelin star restaurant and the experience was phenomenal.  The service was laid back and inviting.  It really puts you at ease.  We did the wine pairing with the meal and it was excellent as well.  About 3-4 different wines and one craft beer were served to us throughout the meal.  If you finish your glass they will happily refill you promptly.  One thing I would do differently on a return trip would be to take it easy on the drinking because it filled me up.  The food was rich, succulent, and surprisingly satiating given the sizes of the dishes.  The service really stood out because of the casualness and friendliness of the staff.  A dish would be brought out and described to you. Any questions were answered with enthusiasm and a smile.  Some dishes weren't always given a full presentation, they were just delivered and named.  It created a well paced dinner.  The time didn't seem to drag once and we were completely saitiated before dessert even came out.  Highly recommended for your Michelin star restaurant needs!
Amazing restaurant. 12 courses.
I definitely recommend this place a thousand times over!

Excellent service, delicious dishes! The menu is fixed, with more than 10-12 plates that create a real culinary experience. Everything, from starters to deserts was a piece of art. Highly recommended, especially for Greek and Mediterranean cuisine lovers!

As expected with a Michelin star restaurant, the dining experience was superb. We were able to get a last minute reservation for a random weekday based on their availability online. They promptly followed up via email and made sure to consider any food allergies or preferences we had. They also verified our preferences when we sat down just to be sure. The small dining area made for an intimate dining experience and everything was exceptionally cooked. The dishes were inventive and perfectly cooked to the point that I wished I could have more. We unfortunately did not do the wine pairing but, even without it, we were at Komi for about 3 hours. The service was very professional as expected. There's limited street parking but a garage just around the corner that was a convenient walk. Overall, I'd definitely consider going back but really only for a special occasion given the $150 per person bill not including wine pairing. The only negative of the night was the $16 glass of Riesling.

This is an okay restaurant nothing served was outstanding or remarkable, and nothing was bad.  Service though was good. Definitely the least memorable of any Michelin starred I've been to and certainly not worth the cost.
Unbelievable!

Spectacular. Each and every detail of every morsel of every bite has been thoughtfully chosen and beautifully prepared. The staff, including the sommelier, are incredibly personable and made us feel like we were part of the family. We cannot wait to go back. Simply unbelievable.
Amazing experience. Delicious and creative food. The staff here is great!!
Celebrated our engagement here with my brother and his fiance, and greatly enjoyed the meal and service. Outstanding experience.

A truly amazing experience- Komi absolutely deserves its Michelin star. Each dish was unique and absolutely delicious.The wine pairing was phenomenal (even had a beer pairing at one point which worked perfectly). Some upscale restaurants leave you wanting, whether it's the amount of food or flavors- Komi provided both (I left the restaurant stuffed and content!) Additionally, the staff was welcoming and the atmosphere basic yet romantic. Will definitely be back again!

Absolutely delicious. Expect approximately 12 courses most of which will be small. The main courses were pretty large though so you should leave feeling satisfied with the amount of food. I usually have the opposite issue where I get full too easily. At Komi, dinner is spaced out over a few hours so it was enough time to eat everything without getting over full.  The food itself definitely stood out. The combination of house brewed birch beer and oven roasted cheese stuffed date was a delicious stand out. The small bites had nicely balanced strong flavors while the mains were well executed more gentle flavors in greater quantity.  Komi maintains a comfortable and upscale atmosphere without feeling oppressivly fancy. Our waiter swapped local restaurant suggestions with us so that was really nice.

An incredible intimate dinning experience with some of the most passionate and animated descriptions of wine I've ever heard. So make sure you get the matching wines!  Delicious adaptions of Mediterranean flavors with excellent (and friendly) service that makes Komi an unforgettable experience.

My first visit in about 8 years. My LAST. Food has changed very little.  TINY bite sized dishes.  Most are so small that 4 servings fit on a small plate.  Amberjack fish came undercooked with lots of bones.  The new lamb neck was greasy and not edible.  The ingredients are far cheaper than they used to be.  Hard wooden seats.  Fairly noisy.  Not worth the very high price.  Not worthy of a Michelin star.  Far overrated.

We came here while on a trip to DC as we wanted to try a Michelin star restaurant and WOW. It was an exceptional experience. Service was phenomenal (thanks Paris for the excellent service) and the food caused our taste buds to have a once in a lifetime explosive experience. They accommodated my meal restrictions. Overall A++++.

(Translated by Google) It's worth every penny you pay. The service is spectacular and the food is from another world. Komi was my first restaurant with a Michelin star and I was really surprised. There are 12 times, the first ones are small and the portions are growing. There is no way you leave hungry. The sommelier's wine selection is impressive, ask him for advice, he will surely suggest something to your liking. You have to make a reservation, there is no way to get there without it. La selección de vinos del somelier es impresionante, pídele recomendación, seguramente te sugerirá algo a tu gusto. Hay que hacer reservación, no hay manera de llegar sin ella. My best eating experience in my entire life. Komi makes you feel like an honored guest, not just a customer. The personable quality of the serving on top of the magnificent food makes for an unforgettable eating experience. I was pregnant when we went to Komi and they made sure to heed my requests of no raw fish or dairy. Even so, the food tasted so great that I could not tell that anything was substituted in place of the original ingredients and recipe.
Loved it!

I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone who would like try something different you will not regret it!!!
We recommend the wine pairing. It added another layer to the experience.

Our family ate at Komi in March. It was a fabulous meal, and the service was impeccable. The goat was a favorite with everyone.
Amazing!  Worth every penny.

(Translated by Google) Until now I have eaten in various restaurants in the world, but it is a restaurant with a high level of scrambling to enter the top 3. I definitely think that it is the top restaurant in Washington DC. I asked for pairing of champagne and wine, but all the courses made me excited by the taste and texture that I have never had before. The bite croquette had a taste like eating a Caesar salad and the shoulder loin of the goat with bone slowly baked for more than 48 hours, so it melted at the moment I put it in my mouth. It was a dish of life number one in the meat dish. Of course the price is expensive, but how do you feel if you come on something anniversary? I think that it will be unforgettable memories. Reservation is mandatory!  (Original) 今迄世界で色々なレストランで食べてきましたが、トップ3に入るめちゃくちゃレベルの高いレストランです。間違いなくワシントンDCではトップレストランだと思います。シャンパンとワインのペアリングを頼みましたが、全てのコースが今までに食べたことがない味や食感で、ワクワクさせてくれました。一口コロッケはなんとシーザーサラダを食べているような味がして、骨付きヤギの肩ロースは48時間以上ゆっくり焼いたいるため、口の中に入れた瞬間溶けてしまいました。肉料理の中で人生ナンバーワンの一品でした。勿論値段は高いですが、何かの記念日に来られては如何でしょうか。忘れられない思い出になるかと思います。予約は必須です！

My husband and I LOVED Komi. It was our first Michelin restaurant experience, and we were blown away by the ambience of understated elegance, the ever-attentive service, and the out-of-this-world delicious Greek-inspired food. There were about twelve delicious courses with a capstone course of fall-off-the-bone, perfectly flavored lamb, home-made pita bread, and incredible sauces. We chose to invest in the wine pairings and did not regret this decision. Their sommelier, Kyle, did an excellent job of telling the stories behind each wine. We experienced a spectrum of wine, from dry, fruity whites to apple cider to earthy, volcanic reds from France, Greece, and Italy. It was an unparalleled experience! Five stars.
Excellent tasting menu experience. Well worth it.
Wonderful. Wonderful food. Great service. Make your plans and GO!

This place is not going to be for everyone. First, it is expensive...for 2 people it is going to be around $450. It is also going to be a long dining experience, as each of the 10 plus courses are served to you slowly. You will perhaps also not enjoy every course, as people's tastes do vary, but your taste buds will truly enjoy the experience. You will taste the salt, the truffle, the Rooibos, the Chamomile, the mint, the honey, and all the other flavors served to you. The staff is well trained, professional and friendly. The place is immaculate and has a nice understated atmosphere. If you can get past the sticker shock, it is a wonderful culinary experience. By the way, there is no menu...it is Chefs Choice only...however, they can accommodate allergies.

One if the best meals I have had in DC

Really fantastic upscale Greek food. The flavors and textures are nuanced, balanced, and interesting throughout all 12+ courses. You won't regret going with the wine pairing ($85) despite the price, they poured 8-9 different wines and beers. Some stand out dishes for us were the green pea anglotti in duck consomme, sea beans and quail egg, bottarga toast, fois gras mousse, goat shank & pitas, and the incredible beet sorbet dessert. Note - they don't allow pictures of the food!

My wife and I ate here Friday night.  It was one of the best dining experiences I have ever had.  Food was exceptional, wine was excellent, the staff (especially Kyle, their wine expert) was amazing, and the  restaurant itself was understated and comfortable.  Could not recommend more highly.
Komi is all about a great culinary experience. Very intimate experience, no complaints whatsoever. Will be back.
Sublime.
Food was outstanding; service was personal, attentive, charismatic, and, well, wonderful. The restaurant is small, but very well staffed with competent and caring people.
It was delicious, I’ve been in 12 out of the 14 Michelin Star restaurants in the dc area, Komi is my second favorite (over the inn at little Washington and minibar)
Great food with great wine. Plates seem small but you will leave full. The wine pairing is generous and you will be a tad typsy.

Amazing food and wine pairing with excellent conversation as well. Each dish came with a proper description and we were given the background and interesting info for each wine.
I've wanted to have dinner here for a long time and I was not disappointed! It was amazing. The staff and food/wine were equally great! It's definitely a splurge, but totally worth it!
A favorite in DC. We’ve been there a few times already, and never disappoints. Great cooking, friendly service, knowledgeable staff. No pictures, by policy.

This is a place where folks go to feel extra uppity and have $500 to waste on bite-size dishes just so they can look cool on Instagram and appear “classy/sophisticated”. If you’re truly hungry and you’re smart with your money, I suggest paying $7 for a gyro at a local mom and pop Greek joint.
Service was spectacular.
An amazingly orchestrated feast from the overture to the finale. Each bite and each morsel increasing the excitement of the meal and the final course does not disappoint by any means.

I gave three stars just because it's still on the list of Michelin list. Besides, the service is good. What I wanna say is the pretty salty food. There were at least three courses which were too salty to bear. Additionally，the main course did make us disappointed. It was served with flat bread with some pork and sources. I have to say it was just like the pancake I ate in China, although the taste was not bad. For the main course，no creativity and surprise as a Michelin restaurant.
Great experience!
Best of you go with adults that are paying for you (i.e. your parents).
There's a reason why they are one of the best in DC.
Very well done. The food was fun. The staff were welcoming and knowledgeable.  It’s an adventure with food. Do the wine pairing. Make reservations. I understand why but it’s a little expensive.
Best dining experience ever!! Exceptional flavors, warm lovely setting and phenomenal customer service.
This is not for a typical restaurant goer but more like a one time thing in life to celebrate on a special day. No doubt food is exceptional but won't be filling and for two, bill was ~ $450
Truly an experience :)  circa 2010
Each visit to KOMI is such an intimate experience with the food and the good people who transform the Delicious food into that experience.
Went to celebrate my girlfriend's birthday, they made us feel extra special and the food was outstanding. The staff breathe a little mystique into an already incredible selection of food.
The meal was fantastic, the service was even better.

I have not been to mini-bar but I've been to bar mini. I just had dinner at Pineapple and Pearls and I'll take Komi over P&P any day.  Great food. Not just inventive and presented well but food I still can taste and crave.  Great service and perfect wine pairings.  I've been here twice and will go back again.
Really good pizza

This cozy, homey Greek tasting menu only restaurant puts you in a setting as if you are in a living room of someone's house. The food was very good and the staff was even better.  Their passion and knowledge of the food and the wine pairings definitely showed through. The only thing I'd change was that you didn't see a menu at any point during your meal. Now personally I enjoy the surprise at the start but sending you home with a printed recap of your evening would be a nice touch that restaurants of similar caliber often provide.  Great for any sort of special occasion or if you are looking for an authentic yet different experience of Greek cuisine.

The most ridiculous meal I had in my entire life. Some tasty bite size appetizers, pasta and pork (main course) were too salty and too basic. Other dishes- nice flavors but nothing mind blowing. Extremely boring long process of waiting for  the next dish to come. This place is classy but plain. Dinner for two with 2 glasses of wine each with tax and tip- $500. Totally not worth it. Folks, if you don't know how to spend  $500 better donate to some charity.
Charming atmosphere, great music, and oh yeah the foods not bad ;p

Went here last Saturday and parking took me ages, they dont offer a valet. But the food was so good and the presentation was superb, i felt like im at a master chef kitchen or something . The price is a bit expensive but its worth the money, not something i can afford often but once in a way yes Only problem is that you need to make a reservation early because restaurant is always crowded.
The food is so well prepared and the flavors are different from what you get at any other restaurant. The server was friendly and very knowledgeable about the menu.
Amazing

Ate here for an early dinner for NYE. Great prix fixe which allowed us to explore the great menu. The service was just as it should be - timely, knowledgable and the MD was excellent. Warm and inviting. Will come back and bring friends.
One of the best meals and services we've ever had! Every course was a delight. Don't skip out on the wine pairings...

Quite an incredible experience to eat at Komi. The dishes are consistent with a Greek-ish theme but are so creative and unique that it's a little difficult to put them into any category beyond high cuisine. The set menu provides many many dishes that arrive in quick succession. Each is a small bite or two until you get to the larger main course (normally a protein like the delicious pork chop we received the night we went) but everything is creative and delicious. I also very much recommend going for the wine pairings. The sommelier is excellent with a vast knowledge of not only where the wine presented to you at the moment is from and it's qualities but also why it complements the current or coming dish. There is a ton of action at this dinner with new courses and pair wines constantly coming your way. There is plenty of time to enjoy both but it is also easy to have paired wines stack up if you get lost in conversation. The only downside to Komi is the price but it's so much the experience and the fine food that I could justify a visit once every few years. Highly recommend for those who can afford it and enjoy the creativity and adventure of high cuisine.

Best meal I ever had. Of course it's expensive, but this one-of-a-kind fusion place is not something you can find anywhere. I went out happy and it's so memorable that I still remember the experience.
Great food and service.
Easily the best meal in DC. Unique courses and flavors. Amazing wine pairings. Prefect pacing. Bon rapport qualité prix.
Real gastro restaurant, good food, nice ambiance
So many interesting flavors and attentive staff.

One of the best meals I've ever had. If you can, arrange your visit so you can do the whole wine flight, as their selection and pairings are outstanding. Many surprising courses, all delicious and memorable - whole firefly squid, a take on a half-smoke, roast goat with a variety of dipping sauces, etc.
We went last year for our anniversary. We loved it so much we decided to make Komi tradition.

Anyplace that  does not publish their menu and prices is a red flag for a place I would never would go to. It's like, they think they are so great they don't have to. That's just marketing hype for gullable fools. Get real people! Tell us what you serve. It's just food.
Unbelievable, like your dreaming.

Worst thing i ever experienced, considering i live in Colorado the food was cold by the time if fricking got here. Worst to-go ever, ILLEGAL REPORTED DEPORTED. And i would give you zero stars but i have to give one so you can see this.
We had a really nice evening with superb dishes
Absolutely wonderful dining experience!  Brought a colleague and enjoyed the food and atmosphere.

What a wonderful place to celebrate a special occasion and to start off our vacation for the first night ! If you are a foodie, this is your place!. It was so much fun letting them surprise us with different things we would have never tried on our own. My husband has had stomach surgery so he cant eat a lot at once. It was perfect how they spread out many courses small portions and each got better and better! I didn't know what to expect by the reviews of people saying it was an "event". But that was a great way to describe it. I was a culinary event worth the money! we got there at 6 and dint leave til around 9 -930. We chose the wine pairing to go with each dish. The second we walked in, they wished us a Happy Anniversary and when we left they wrote Happy 27th Anniversary on a cute little box that had our dessert in it.  It was so much fun and the food was fantastic! The waiters and waitresses were not stuffy, but full of personality and knowledge. Cant say enough about this experience.We had never been to anything like it. Its a very small place and you need to call weeks in advance to get a reservation. And getting an early reservation worked out perfect because it takes several hours. We enjoyed it so much I want to  go back to DC just to  go there again. A ++++++++++  Dootsie & Miller Williams B'ham, AL

A little persistence on the phone really pays off. We had a lady weekend and got a reservation for 7:30pm on a Friday. The food was amazing. The first several seafood bites were refreshing and balanced, and there was an incredible beet/tomato tartare. The highlight was definitely the pork (large format). The staff was friendly and knowledgeable and it was a fantastic wine pairing. It was nearly a 3.5 hour dinner. Great experience, and one of my favorite tastings.
Nice
It was a pleasant night and a good experience.

Very good experience. After my friends told me about this restaurant I thought it was a small place. But no, it's middle sized and really nice inside. They have interesting and pretty long line of small tasting menu appetizers, 2 small dishes of different great pasta after and pretty big main course. They really care if you are starved because they are ready to bring you more main course for free if you want. Wine paring was good, a bit monotonous cause it was 1 sort of wine to two dishes, but for $70 for wine paring it's good, especially when sommelier is eager to refill your glass every time it's empty. Service was amazing. Thank you, guys!
Komi, my wife and I enjoyed our 5th anniversary culinary experience at your restaurant. Thank you for helping with all her surprises (Good job to whoever chose the Peonies arrangement).
I love it it is very accurate

"We can accommodate many dietary restrictions, though we are not able to create a version of dinner that avoids egg or dairy." Well, at least you're honest up front, but all this really means is you're just too full of yourselves to try because you could if you wanted to.
Excellent service and food. Did not miss a beat. The food was great and service exceptional.
The best meal/ food experience I have ever had. Absolutely unreal. Service is beyond top notch as well. Was expecting a great night out but I was just blown away. You have to go!

Love Komi. Their attention to detail is impeccable. Everything that comes out of the kitchen is perfect, super creative.  Service is outstanding, probably because it's obvious that the servers love their jobs.  One complaint - been a few times in the past year, and every time have received the lamb and/or goat gyros as an entree, which a) isn't the absolute best and b) mix it up a little! :)

The Food was great as was the wine pairing, but the front end of the house needs some work.  While the wait staff were generally efficient and friendly.  The wine sommelier was to say the least a little short with explanations.  The whole point of a wine pairing is to present the wine, describe what you are serving, and why this particular wine is an important compliment to this course of food.  Sadly, our Sommelier acted as though he was doing us a favor by answering our questions.  The overall experience was good.  The food was great, and it appears to be a nice place, but in comparison the wait staff at Duck Tavern for example if far more professional.

I have been wanting to go to Komi for years. I finally got the chance last Friday when my husband and I went in celebration of our 3rd anniversary.  I would have initially given the restaurant a 4 out of 5 but my husband got food poisoning and didn't even make it to our last dessert course. He spent the rest of our anniversary in the bathroom ill. For a restaurant with this kind of reputation and with this pricetag, food poisoning should not have been on the menu at all.

Komi deserves every bit of praise it receives. Food is inventive, unique, exquisitely presented, and delicious. Flavors you wouldn't think to pair are expertly presented as perfect complements. The space is simple yet elegant; minimalist and comfortable. Service is out of this world. Abundantly friendly, happy to be there, eager to please, and anticipating your every whim. The sommelier knows his stuff — trust him and it will elevate your meal to a new level. Spring for the wine pairing. It's expertly crafted and worth every penny.

This is, I think, as close to perfect as you can get in DC.  The food is spectacular -- clever, imaginative and absolutely laugh-out-loud delicious. The service is the best I've had in DC -- attentive, knowledgeable, prompt -- and then invisible.  When we went they sat only 2- and 4-person parties, which makes for more effective, dramatic service.  This place really is about the food.  Don't look at the bill, although it's worth every penny.

So few things in life are everything they're built up to be...but Komi met...and exceeded our expectations.  Everything about our experience was outstanding!  Our reservation was for 9:15.  We were seated immediately...and by 9:18...we were sipping champagne and enjoying the first course.  If you're in a hurry...this isn't the place for you.  We were there for more than three incredible hours...savoring one surprise after another! Multiple courses (we lost count!) and each one delivered a "Wow!" From Komi staples like the olive oil date...to a home run main course of goat shoulder with pita bread and a dish featuring 5 different accompaniments. I've never had goat prior to my dinner at Komi...and it was awesome!  A nice outer crust and delicate and tender meat all the way through.  We opted for the wine paring...and our glassed were never empty.  The sommelier is not stingy with his choices...and quick to offer an alternative if he senses that you're not enjoying the wine. The wait staff was super-friendly...very attentive...and seemed genuinely excited to present each dish and curious to know if we enjoyed the offerings. When I informed someone on staff that I'd have to interrupt service for a few minutes to retrieve my vehicle...which was parked in a nearby garage that was about to close...I was told to relax and not worry.  At the end of the night...the same gentleman escorted us from the restaurant to the parking garage...where he produced a key card that got us in to get our car.  We'll definitely return...and we'll eagerly recommend Komi to our friends...and anyone else seeking a genuinely special dining experience in Washington.
The best restaurant in DC. Tasting menu will blow your taste buds away. Service is exceptional. Make a reservation one month in advance.
Excelent experience.Very creative, challenging and yet tastefull food. Serice top notch. Wine list offers good values although te pairing is also a good deal. Loved it!

Took my boyfriend here for his birthday, and we were both amazed at the greatness of not only the food, but also the service.  We were even treated to a second round of spanakopita bites after my boyfriend raved about them.They even confirmed my food allergy before the meal, and gave my boyfriend a birthday "present" to enjoy. Service was outstanding.Overall this was the best meal I have eaten in DC, and I will definitely be saving to head back again soon. Perfect date restaurant and very casual while still maintaining that fine dining experience.

It's street food masquerading as haute cuisine in all the worst ways. The dishes lack any sort of finesse or imagination, but they are presented in a format and at a price (oh god, the price) which would suggest otherwise.  I don't mind paying for really good stuff, but I do mind paying an order of magnitude too much for merely ok street food.
You want to think it's too precious --- and then they wow you every time with perfect service, stunning food, and a great atmosphere.
Hands down, the best restaurant in the DC metro area. Komi's food is unsurpassed and the service is the best I've had on the Eastern seaboard.
A Theatre of the Taste Buds in 16+ 'acts'!  Well deserving of a standing ovation at the end.

AMAZING service, great food.  By "amazing" service, I mean, near psychic.  I ordered a drink, didn't like it, didn't complain.  The sommelier comes over and says, I don't think you liked that, try this instead.  What she chose was fantastic.  The servers asked about allergies and dislikes, and each of us was served in compliance with the answers.  The only downside (and I mean the ONLY one) is that they don't take parties larger than four.  Otherwise, highly recommended.

Ho. Ly. Bleep.  We actually got a reservation to KOMI and had a ridiculous meal.  We had the braised goat (for 2) when we went with a variety of other appetizers and loved everything about it.  If you can get a reservation, you're in for a treat.
One of the best resturants in DC

one of the best meals i've ever had.  service is friendly, knowledgeable.  decor is pleasant, with ample space between tables - and also unpretentious.  the food just wowed us.  a great value for the wonderful quality.
One of the best dining experiences of my life.  The service was absolutely perfect, and even after all those courses, we left feeling just great.  That is a feat!  A truly wonderful experience.
